'''Mino Agatanushi Shrine''' (みのあがたぬしじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Yao|Q490872|qid=Q490872|1=Yao, Osaka}}, {{ill|lt=Osaka Prefecture|Q122723|qid=Q122723|1=Osaka Prefecture}}. It is a {{ill|lt=Shikinaisha small shrine|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}, and its former shrine rank was village shrine.

=== History / Overview ===
It is the tutelary shrine of former Kaminoshima Village (Kaminoshima area of Yao City) in old {{ill|lt=Kawachi Province|Q1047150|qid=Q1047150|1=Kawachi Province}}{{ill|lt=Kawachi District (Osaka)|Q11553458|qid=Q11553458|lt=Kawachi District|1=Kawachi district}}. It enshrines the ancestral deity of powerful families that once ruled this area: the Mino no Muraji and Mino Agatanushi line.

The date of foundation is unknown, but because the {{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}} records two seats of Mino Agatanushi Shrine in {{ill|lt=Wakae District|Q11616589|qid=Q11616589|1=Wakae district}}, Kawachi Province, it is considered to have existed before the Heian period. In Meiji 5 (1872), it was ranked as {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|qid=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.

The west side of the precinct is a small rise, the former embankment trace of {{ill|lt=Tamagushi River|Q11572360|qid=Q11572360|lt=Tamagushi River|1=Tamagushi River}} (old {{ill|lt=Yamato River|Q9001527|qid=Q9001527|1=Yamato River}}), once flowing on the west side. It is said to survive only here today. It is designated as protected woodland by Yao City and is a valuable historic site. South of the precinct is Mino Agata Pond.

=== Festivals ===
* July 2 - Summer festival
* Second Saturday/Sunday of October - Autumn festival (futon-daiko procession)

=== Other ===
* {{ill|lt=2022|Q49625|qid=Q49625|1=2022}}, appeared on TV Tokyo’s {{ill|lt=Emergency SOS! We Drained the Pond!|Q30938102|qid=Q30938102|1=Emergency SOS! We Drained the Pond!}}

=== Shikibe-no-Miya ===
[[ファイル:Shikibe-Minoagatanushi Jinja01.JPG|thumb|right|200px|Shikibe Mino Agatanushi Shrine]]
Slightly south of the main shrine, by Higashiyamamotochō 5-chōme Park, there is another seat called “Shikibe Mino Agatanushi Shrine” (Shikibe-no-Miya). It has only a shrine building on a small plot. This place was at the edge of a settlement in former {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Takayasu District|1=UNKNOWN}}{{ill|lt=Higashiyamamotochō|Q11526717|qid=Q11526717|lt=Manganji Village|1=Higashiyamamotochō}}; in the mid-Edo period, when the village split in a water-rights dispute and the Shikibe settlement moved south to Manganji Village, a divided spirit was invited there.

